<body>
  <p class="title">According to Modal Verb</p>
  <p>‘will’ 
<br><br>
Direct: Rita said to me, “You will go home tomorrow.”
<br><br>
‘would’  
<br><br>
Indirect: Rita said to me that I would go home next day.
</p><p>
‘shall’ 
<br><br>
Direct: Refat said, “I shall do the work.” 
<br><br>
‘should’ 
<br><br>
Indirect: Refat said that he should do the work.
</p><p>
‘Can’ 
<br><br>
Direct: He said, “I can finish the work.”
<br><br>
‘Could’ 
<br><br>
Indirect: He said that he could finish the work.
</p><p>
‘May’ 
<br><br>
Direct: Pritam said, “I may go to school”. 
<br><br>
‘Might’ 
<br><br>
Indirect: Pritam said that he might go to school.

</p>
<br>
<p>Wish, would, rather, sooner, it is high time এর পর unreal past tense অপরিবর্তিত থাকে।
<br><br>
Direct: He said, “It is time we left the place.
<br><br>
Indirect: He said that it was time they left the place.
</p>
<p>Indirect speech এ “had better” 1st person এবং third person এর সহিত অপরিবর্তিত থাকে। কিন্তু second person-এর সহিত had better    অপরিবর্তিত থাকতে পারে অথবা নিম্নলিখিত উপায়ে পরিবর্তিত হতে পারে।
<br><br>
Direct: He said to me,”You had better go”.
<br><br>
Indirect: He said to me that i had better go.
</p>
<p>might, ought to, should, would, used to, indirect speech এ অপরিবর্তিত থাকে।
<br><br>
Direct: I said to him,”You might go”.
<br><br>
Indirect: I said to him that he might go.
</p>
<p>If i were you, I should/would… ” দ্বারা উপদেশ বুঝালে indirect করার সময় subject+advise+object+to+reported speech এর verb বসে।
<br><br>
Direct: I said to him,” If i were you, i should wait”.
<br><br>
Indirect: I advised him to want.
</p>
